history.content:
In my opinion, in order of usefulness: EE 127, Math 110, EE 126, then Stat 134 (I've only taken the first three).

But it's just as valid to take them after CS 189, which is what I did. CS 189 motivated me to take those other classes.

children.subject:
I think it also depends on who is teaching and their style of teaching. For example, I'm taking 189 this semester with Recht and Malik. In my opinion, I feel like the course taught by them is heavier on the math and proofs of the formulas than other classes (our midterm was all derivation/math problems compared to multiple choice / true false questions from previous exams). Not to say that 189 is not a math heavy course, it's very important to make sure you take the prereqs seriously if you want to do well, but I feel like currently I would do so much better if I had taken Math 110 or EE 126 or even Stat 135 before this class.

I would definitely recommend at least taking either Math 110 or EE 126 before this class. Of course the best preparation you can do is take EE 127. According to Recht, if you take that class and understand the material, CS 189 becomes an easy class.

I didn't take any of those classes (not even CS 188) and did fine in 189 with Shewchuk last semester. Since Shewchuk is teaching it next semester, I think you'll be fine without doing any of them really. Just make sure you know the content from 53, 54, and CS 70 REALLY well. 

If I had to pick any of the classes you've listed, I'd say Stat 134. 110 and 126 would be overdoing it IMO
